ites%2C%20including%20Mahadev%20Book%20and%20Reddyannaprestopro%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20government%20said%20in%20the%20statement%20via%20the%20Press%20Information%20Bureau%20(PIB).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20action%20follows%20investigations%20conducted%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20against%20illegal%20betting%20app%20syndicate%20and%20subsequent%20raids%20on%20Mahadev%20Book%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20revealing%20the%20app's%20unlawful%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20government%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20action%20comes%20on%20a%20day%20when%20an%20accused%20in%20a%20money%20laundering%20case%20claimed%20that%20Chhattisgarh%20Chief%20Minister%20Bhupesh%20Baghel%20had%20asked%20him%20to%20go%20to%20the%20UAE.%20The%20accused%2C%20Shubham%20Soni%2C%20who%20is%20wanted%20by%20the%20ED%20for%20alleged%20money%20laundering%2C%20made%20a%20video%20from%20Dubai%20in%20which%20he%20made%20the%20serious%20allegation%20against%20Mr%20Baghel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20involves%20allegations%20of%20money%20laundering%20and%20use%20of%20illegal%20funds%20during%20election%20against%20Mr%20Baghel%2C%20which%20comes%20days%20before%20Chhattisgarh%20is%20expected%20to%20vote.%20Chhattisgarh%20is%20the%20only%20state%20where%20the%20Congress%20is%20seen%20as%20being%20on%20a%20strong%20wicket.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnion%20Minister%20Rajeev%20Chandrasekhar%20in%20the%20statement%20today%20indicated%20the%20Chhattisgarh%20government%20could%20have%20shut%20down%20the%20illegal%20app%20and%20website%20long%20ago%20as%20it%20%26quot%3Bhad%20all%20the%20power%26quot%3B%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Chhattisgarh%20government%20had%20all%20the%20power%20to%20recommend%20shutting%20down%20of%20the%20website%2Fapp%20under%20Section%2069A%20IT%20(Information%20Technology)%20Act.%20However%2C%20they%20did%20not%20do%20so%20and%20no%20such%20request%20is%20made%20by%20the%20state%20government%20while%20they%20have%20been%20investigatin