%20studying%20the%20curious%20creatures%2C%20researchers%20on%20the%20project%20also%20believe%20they%20have%20revealed%20new%20evidence%20that%20Punt%20and%20Adulis%2C%20two%20legendary%20trading%20regions%20that%20shaped%20the%20world's%20economic%20and%20geopolitical%20structure%2C%20may%20have%20been%20the%20same%20place%20in%20the%20coastal%20region%20in%20Eritrea%E2%80%94%20separated%20by%20a%20thousand%20years%20of%20history.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mummified%20hamadryas%20baboons%20were%20found%20in%201905%2C%20eroding%20out%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fegypt-archaeologists-uncover-ancient-coffins-colorful-carvings-intact-2019-10%5C%22%3Evalley%20of%20the%20monkeys%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20an%20archaeological%20site%20at%20Luxor's%20western%20bank%20of%20the%20Nile%20known%20for%20its%20depictions%20of%20baboons%20on%20tomb%20walls%20discovered%20nearby.%20The%20creatures%20were%20missing%20their%20ferocious%20canine%20teeth%2C%20but%2C%20unlike%20other%20mummified%20baboon%20specimens%20found%20from%20the%20same%20timeframe%2C%20they%20were%20neither%20entombed%20with%20noblemen%20of%20the%20time%20nor%20found%20in%20group%20catacombs%2C%20raising%20questions%20for%20decades%20about%20how%20they%20got%20there%20%E2%80%94%20and%20why.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScience%20has%20finally%20advanced%20enough%20to%20answer%20some%20lingering%20questions%20about%20the%20baboons.%20After%20testing%20ten%20different%20specimens%20and%20being%20able%20to%20extract%20DNA%20from%20just%20a%20single%20one%2C%20Gisela%20Kopp%2C%20a%20biologist%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Konstanz%2C%20utilized%20a%20new%20method%20of%20genetic%20analysis%20on%20DNA%20from%20the%20specimen%20to%20trace%20its%20origins.%20Kopp's%20discovery%20is%20the%20first%20time%20ancient%20DNA%20from%20a%20mummified%20non-human%20primate%20has%20successfully%20been%20analyzed%20to%20this%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMythic%20ancient%20cities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mummy%20Kopp%20extracted%20DNA%20from%20%E2%80%94%20estimated%20to%20date%20back%20to%20between%20800%20and%20500%20BCE%20%E2%80%94%20corroborated%20findings%20that%20the%20Horn%20of%20Africa%20was%20the%20baboons'%20region%20of%20origin%20when%20compared%20with%20a%20similar%20sample%20that%20had%20previously%20been%20unearthed.%20The%20genetics%20of%20Kopp's%20baboon%20were%20compared%20to%20another%20sample%20that%20originated%20from%20the%20coastal%20region%20in%20Eritrea%2C%20where%2C%20in%20ancient%20times%2C%20the%20port%20of%20Adulis%20was%20likely%20located.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Kopp's%20baboon%20was%20preserved%20long%20before%20the%20ancient%20city%20of%20Adulis%20flourished%20as%20a%20key%20trading%20center%20and%20port%2C%20where%20animals%20like%20baboons%20and%20leopards%20were%20frequently%20bought%20and%20sold.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAncient%20texts%20from%20the%20same%20time%20period%20suggest%20Kopp's%20baboon%20likely%20originated%20in%20a%20city%20called%20Punt.%20The%20exact%20location%20of%20Punt%2C%20Kopp%20told%20Insider%2C%20has%20long%20puzzled%20researchers%20due%20to%20references%20to%20the%20town%20being%20found%20in%20significant%20texts%20and%20artwork%20but%20not%20found%20on%20existing%20maps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20specimen%20we%20studied%20fits%20chronologically%20with%20the%20last%20known%20expeditions%20to%20Punt.%20Geographically%2C%20however%2C%20it%20fits%20Adulis%2C%20a%20location%20that%2C%20centuries%20later%2C%20was%20known%20as%20a%20trading%20place%2C%20also%20for%20primates.%20We%20hypothesize%20that%20Punt%20and%20Adulis%20are%20two%20different%20names%20for%20the%20same%20place%20that%20were%20used%20at%20different%20points%20in%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Kopp%20wrote%20in%20a%20research%20paper%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2023%2F10%2F231024110554.htm%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20only%20after%20we%20put%20our%20biological%20findings%20in%20the%20context%20of%20historical%20research%20that%20the%20story%20really%20came%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223055%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20skull%20and%20linen%20wrapping%20of%20a%20mummified%20baboon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653deca296f7540cd068b1ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222293%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpecimen%2090001206%2C%20held%20by%20the%20Musee%20des%20Confluences%2C%20Lyon%2C%20France%3A%20Skull%20and%20linen%20wrapping%20of%20a%20mummified%20baboon%20recovered%20from%20Gabbanat%20el-Qurud%2C%20Egypt%20and%20connected%20genetically%20to%20coastal%20Eritrea.%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Ageneau%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EKopp%20told%20Insider%20the%20exact%20methods%20behind%20importing%20the%20primates%20to%20Egypt%2C%20raising%20them%2C%20and%20then%20eventually%20mummifying%20them%20remains%20unclear.%20So%2C%20too%2C%20is%20precisely%20how%20Egyptians%20came%20to%20know%20of%20baboons%20in%20the%20first%20place%20since%20they%20weren't%20native%20to%20the%20region.%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20the%20way%20that%20they're%20presented%20in%20the%20artwork%2C%20they%20must%20have%20observed%20the%20baboons%20in%20their%20natural%20habitat%2C%26quot%3B%20Kopp%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20spot%20on%2C%20how%20they%20hold%20the%20postures%2C%20and%20the%20different%20behaviors%20%E2%80%94%20they%20must%20have%20observed%20them%20in%20their%20natural%20habitats%2C%20but%20we%20don't%20know%20why%2C%20or%20how.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPesky%20baboons%2C%20a%20godly%20embodiment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropologist%20Nathaniel%20Dominy%20from%20Dartmouth%20College%2C%20who%20collaborated%20with%20Kopp%20on%20the%20study%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20baboons%20are%20often%20conspicuously%20missing%20from%20African%20artworks%20of%20the%20time%20due%20to%20their%20reputation%20as%20pests%20in%20their%20natural%20habitats%20but%20they%20hold%20special%20significance%20in%20Egypt.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThroughout%20Africa%2C%20you'll%20see%20loads%20of%20elephants%20and%20giraffes%2C%20and%20all%20kinds%20of%20products%20representing%20animals%2C%20but%20very%20rarely%20baboons.%20And%20it's%20because%2C%20in%20general%2C%20baboons%20are%20not%20well-liked.%20They%20raid%20your%20crops%2C%20they%20destroy%20your%20livelihood%2C%20they%20are%20harbingers%20of%20disease%2C%26quot%3B%20Dominy%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20remember%20going%20to%20Egypt%20for%20the%20first%20time%20and%20just%20being%20astounded%20by%20the%20number%20of%20baboons%20being%20depicted%20on%20temple%20walls%2C%20or%20in%20the%20tombs%20of%20nobles%20you'd%20see%20large%20statues%20of%20baboons%20at%20various%20temples.%20And%20they%20even%20mummified%20baboons%2C%20which%20any%20primatologist%20will%20tell%20you%20is%20puzzling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDominy%20said%20for%20ancient%20Egyptians%2C%20baboons%20appear%20to%20have%20served%20a%20dual%20spiritual%20purpose.%20The%20creatures%20are%20often%20shown%20with%20their%20arms%20raised%20toward%20the%20sun%20in%20what%20he%20described%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bposture%20of%20adoration%26quot%3B%20toward%20the%20rising%20sun%2C%20the%20Egyptian%20god%20Rah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20researchers%20speculate%20that%20baboons%20would%20naturally%20orient%20their%20bodies%20toward%20the%20rising%20sun%20and%20that%20they%20would%20vocalize%20at%20the%20rising%20sun%2C%26quot%3B%20Dominy%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20idea%20is%20that%20ancient%20Egyptians%20would%20have%20seen%20this%20natural%20behavior%2C%20and%20it%20would%20have%20resonated%20strongly%20with%20them%20because%20the%20Egyptians%20would%20greet%20the%20rising%20sun%2C%20and%20they%20would%20sing%20to%20the%20rising%20sun.%20And%20so%20this%20might%20have%20been%20just%20this%20amazing%2C%20tantalizing%20animal%20that%20was%20connected%20to%20their%20own%20religious%20practices.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaboons%20were%20also%20frequently%20depicted%20as%20the%20physical%20embodiment%20of%20the%20god%20Thoth%2C%20the%20Egyptian%20moon%20deity%C2%A0and%20the%20god%20associated%20with%20wisdom%20and%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20they%20can%20both%20represent%20the%20moon%20god%20and%20the%20god%20of%20wisdom%2C%20but%20they%20are%20also%20showing%20their%20loyalty%20to%20the%20Sun%20god%2C%20Rah%2C%26quot%3B%20Dominy%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20for%20us%2C%20at%20this%20point%2C%20to%20understand%20that%20is%20difficult%2C%20but%20it%20just%20seemed%20like%20the%20importance%20of%20baboons%20is%20this%20kind%20of%20ability%20for%20them%20to%20bridge%20both%20the%20sun%20and%20the%20moon%2C%20the%20two%20most%20important%20celestial%20bodies%20for%20the%20Egyptians.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20religious%20significance%20may%20have%20driven%20the%20Egyptian's%20desire%20to%20import%2C%20raise%2C%20and%20preserve%20the%20creatures%2C%20Dominy%20and%20Kopp%20hypothesize.%20Their%20canine%20teeth%2C%20so%20powerful%20they%20can%20slice%20a%20human%20thigh%20to%20the%20bone%20in%20a%20single%20bite%2C%C2%A0were%20likely%20removed%20as%20a%20safety%20measure.%20Though%20it%20remains%20unclear%20if%20the%20buyers%20or%20sellers%20of%20the%20baboons%20removed%20them%2C%20Dominy%20said%20there%20was%20clear%20evidence%20that%20the%20teeth%20were%20removed%20early%20in%20life%2C%20as%20new%20bone%20had%20begun%20to%20regrow%20over%20the%20gap%20left%20by%20the%20extraction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20full%20meaning%20and%20significance%20behind%20the%20keeping%20and%20mummification%20of%20baboons%20in%20Egypt%20may%20never%20be%20known%2C%20the%20new%20knowledge%20provided%20by%20analyzing%20the%20monkeys'%20DNA%20provides%20a%20missing%20link%20in%20understanding%20how%20international%20trade%20developed%20in%20the%20region%20eventually%20shaped%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20drove%20maritime%20technology%2C%20this%20drove%20industry%2C%20this%20was%20an%20economic%20catalyst.%20I%20mean%2C%20their%20motives%20to%20get%20baboons%20%E2%80%94%20it%20changed%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Dominy%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20know%20that's%20a%20big%20claim%2C%20but%20that%20link%20between%20Egypt%20and%20Adulis%20is%20the%20first%20major%20leg%20of%20what%20would%20become%20known%20as%20the%20maritime%20spice%20route.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20spice%20route%2C%20you%20know%2C%20I'm%20speaking%20English%20now%20because%20of%20that%20spice%20route.%20The%20geopolitical%20importance%20of%20the%20spice%20route%20would%20shape%20our%20world%20in%20profound%20ways%2C%20and%20the%20relationship%20between%20Egypt%20and%20Adulis%20really%20is%20the%20first%20step%20in%20what%20many%20researchers%20call%20the%20beginnings%20of%20economic%20globalization.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmysterious-mummified-baboons-egypt-answers-gift-god-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699193101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653dc8cb356802a56be6d693%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmysterious-mummified-baboons-egypt-answers-gift-god-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mummified%20baboons%20found%20in%20Egypt%20puzzled%20scientists%20because%20they%20weren't%20native%20to%20the%20area.%20Researchers%20believe%20they%20were%20imported%20as%20gifts%20to%20gods.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktangalakislippert%40insider.com%20(Katherine%20Tangalakis-Lippert)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A42%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmysterious-mummified-baboons-egypt-answers-gift-god-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Alief%2C%20Indie%20Distributor%20Indican%20Pictures%20Cement%20Deal%20On%20Santiago%20Fillol%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%99Matadero%2C%E2%80%99%20a%20%E2%80%98Paranoid%20Giallo%20Meets%20Political%20Thriller%E2%80%99%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699192995000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2FMatadero-Still-5.png%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D527%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235780512%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22West%20Hollywood-based%20indie%20distribution%20outfit%20Indican%20Pictures%20(%E2%80%9CGossamer%20Folds%E2%80%9D)%20has%20secured%20North%20American%20rights%20for%20Santiago%20Fillol%E2%80%99s%20political%20thriller%20%E2%80%9CMatadero%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%9CSlaughterhouse%E2%80%9D).%C2%A0%20The%20debut%20fiction%20feature%20from%20the%20Argentine%20director%20saw%20its%20world%20premiere%20in%20competition%20at%20Locarno%20in%202022%2C%20with%20further%20festival%20bows%20at%20Mar%20Del%20Plata%20and%20Seville%20before%20December%20theatrical%20runs%20in%20Argentina%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Falief-indican-matadero-santiago-fillol-1235780512%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Falief-indican-matadero-santiago-fillol-1235780512%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Falief-indican-matadero-santiago-fillol-1235780512%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ananya%20celebrates%20birthday%20with%20Suhana%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699192573000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104989650%2Cimgsize-38788.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fananya-panday-celebrates-her-birthday-with-suhana-khan-and-friends-in-mumbai-after-returning-from-hol