%20mile%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20thought%20it%20might%20also%20act%20as%20a%20catalyst%20for%20serious%20worldwide%20improvement%20in%20fast%20bowling.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20despite%20continuing%20improvement%20in%20the%20athletic%20ability%20of%20fast%20bowlers%2C%20the%20magical%20three-figure%20barrier%20has%20only%20been%20surpassed%20since%20by%20Brett%20Lee%20and%20Shaun%20Tait%20%E2%80%93%20and%20not%20for%20over%20ten%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHas%20cricket%20fast%20bowling%E2%80%99s%20top%20speed%20stalled%3F%20During%20the%20current%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cricketworldcup.com%2F%5C%22%3E2023%20One-Day%20International%20Men%E2%80%99s%20World%20Cup%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20hosted%20in%20India%2C%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20bowlers%20have%20produced%20speeds%20over%2090mph%20(145km%20per%20hour)%2C%20with%20the%20fastest%20being%20around%2095mph%20(153%20km%20per%20hour).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20performance%20of%20cricket%20fast%20bowlers%20almost%20entirely%20depends%20on%20two%20factors.%20The%20first%20is%20the%20amount%20of%20momentum%20developed%20in%20the%20run-up%20and%20maintained%20before%20the%20front%20foot%20contacting%20the%20floor.%20The%20second%20is%20the%20technique%20employed%20to%20generate%20and%20transfer%20momentum%20within%20the%20body%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FBowling_action%23%2Fmedia%2FFile%3ABowling_action.png%5C%22%3Eduring%20the%20bowling%20phase%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20the%20front%20foot%20contacting%20the%20floor%20and%20the%20release%20of%20the%20ball%20from%20the%20bowler%E2%80%99s%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.humankinetics.com%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Fjab%2F29%2F1%2Farticle-p78.xml%5C%22%3EPrevious%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20highlighted%20that%20the%20fastest%20elite%20male%20bowlers%20generate%20more%20momentum%20in%20their%20run-up%2C%20adopting%20a%20movement%20strategy%20that%20aims%20to%20maintain%20and%20transfer%20this%20momentum%20into%20the%20throw%20instead%20of%20generating%20additional%20momentum%20from%20their%20muscles.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETesting%20the%20limits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20investigate%20the%20limits%20of%20fast%20bowling%20performance%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flinkinghub.elsevier.com%2Fretrieve%2Fpii%2FS0021929023003354%5C%22%3Eworld-leading%20predictive%20musculoskeletal%20computer%20simulation%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20ten%20elite%20male%20fast%20bowlers%20(essentially%20a%20virtual%20clone%20of%20each%20bowler)%20was%20developed.%20It%20then%20optimised%20their%20technique%20to%20maximise%20the%20release%20speed%20of%20the%20ball.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20none%20of%20these%20bowlers%20were%20predicted%20by%20the%20computer%20model%20to%20break%20the%20100mph%20barrier.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20why%20the%20top%20speed%20has%20stalled%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20consider%20how%20all%20the%20factors%20influencing%20human%20movement%20patterns%20affect%20the%20technique%20of%20fast%20bowlers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.2165%2F00007256-200333040-00001%5C%22%3EThe%20behaviour%20of%20all%20our%20movement%20patterns%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20shaped%20by%20three%20types%20of%20constraint.%20The%20first%20is%20organismic%3A%20these%20are%20constraints%20on%20the%20individual%2C%20such%20as%20their%20size%2C%20strength%20and%20range%20of%20motion.%20The%20second%20factor%20shaping%20movement%20patterns%20is%20the%20environment%20the%20individual%20interacts%20with%2C%20including%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20temperature%2C%20equipment%20and%20surfaces.%20The%20third%20shaping%20factor%20is%20the%20task%2C%20which%20involves%20constraints%20such%20as%20the%20goal%20of%20the%20activity%2C%20the%20rules%20and%20the%20intensity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOur%20previous%20experiences%20of%20the%20movement%20%E2%80%93%20what%20we%20have%20seen%2C%20what%20we%20have%20been%20told%20and%20our%20previous%20performance%20of%20the%20movement%20%E2%80%93%20also%20affect%20individual%20technique%20in%20fast%20bowling.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20innate%20physiology%20of%20the%20fast%20bowler%2C%20an%20organismic%20constraint%2C%20provides%20the%20only%20potential%20area%20for%20development%20in%20fast%20bowling.%20The%20other%20constraints%2C%20such%20as%20environment%20and%20task%2C%20which%20often%20lead%20to%20scientific%20and%20technological%20development%20associated%20with%20improvements%20in%20other%20sports%2C%20are%20extremely%20limited%20in%20fast%20bowling.%20This%20is%20due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20equipment%20and%20the%20simplicity%20of%20the%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20physiological%20aspect%20often%20considered%20to%20be%20associated%20with%20improvements%20in%20fast%20bowling%20performance%20is%20an%20increase%20in%20muscular%20strength%2C%20power%20and%20endurance.%20However%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20unique%20cricket%20bowling%20%E2%80%9Ctask%E2%80%9D%20constraint%20which%20requires%20bowlers%20to%20maintain%20a%20straight%20arm%20during%20the%20bowling%20phase.%20This%20significantly%20reduces%20the%20time%20available%20to%20complete%20the%20throwing%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExplosive%20activation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EElite%20males%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F02640414.2018.1522700%5C%22%3Ecomplete%20the%20bowling%20phase%20in%20approximately%20100%20milliseconds%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20similar%20to%20the%20time%20required%20to%20explosively%20activate%20a%20single%20muscle.%20This%20limits%20the%20ability%20of%20bowlers%20to%20develop%20additional%20momentum%20using%20their%20muscles%20in%20the%20bowling%20phase%20and%20neutralises%20the%20effect%20of%20strength%20increases%20on%20ball%20speed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20explains%20why%20maximising%20momentum%20generated%20during%20the%20run-up%20is%20preferred%20over%20generating%20muscular%20momentum%20during%20the%20bowling%20phase.%20It%20also%20explains%20why%20fast%20bowling%20top%20speeds%20have%20not%20increased%20despite%20recent%20advances%20in%20fast%20bowlers%E2%80%99%20athletic%20abilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F02640414.2018.1522700%5C%22%3Eresearch%20on%20women%20fast%20bowlers%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20highlighted%20that%20bowlers%20who%20generate%20less%20momentum%20during%20the%20run-up%20and%20therefore%20have%20more%20time%20available%20to%20generate%20additional%20muscular%20momentum%2C%20adopt%20a%20movement%20pattern%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.assaf.org.za%2Findex.php%2Fsajsm%2Farticle%2Fview%2F15080%5C%22%3Emore%20akin%20to%20throwing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20this%20approach%2C%20the%20momentum%20generated%20in%20the%20run-up%20is%20added%20to%20via%20the%20use%20of%20large%20rotational%20torso%20muscles%20within%20the%20bowling%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EImprovements%20to%20the%20performance%20of%20the%20large%20rotational%20torso%20muscles%20in%20men%20and%20women%20could%20possibly%20improve%20the%20generation%20of%20muscular%20momentum.%20But%20this%20approach%20is%20considered%20a%20sub-optimal%20technique%20by%20the%20research%20that%E2%80%99s%20been%20carried%20out%20on%20fast%20bowling.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20potential%20mechanism%20to%20increase%20the%20time%20available%20to%20develop%20more%20momentum%20from%20muscles%20would%20be%20to%20increase%20the%20range%20of%20motion%20that%20joints%20move%20through%20during%20the%20bowling%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoint%20%E2%80%98hypermobility%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F02640414.2023.2200520%5C%22%3ERecent%20research%20has%20highlighted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2C%20on%20average%2C%20elite%20fast%20bowlers%20with%20an%20increased%20range%20of%20motion%20in%20the%20hip%20and%20shoulder%20had%20greater%20ball%20release%20speeds.%20It%20was%20also%20suggested%20that%20the%20bowlers%E2%80%99%20techniques%20were%20probably%20influenced%20by%20their%20range%20of%20motion%20during%20their%20early%20learning%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20elbow%20hyperextension%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20joint%20travels%20beyond%20a%20straight%20position%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F02640414.2015.1137340%5C%22%3Ehas%20been%20shown%20to%20increase%20the%20speed%20of%20ball%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20up%20to%205%25%20during%20the%20bowling%20phase.%20A%20common%20misconception%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%20taller%20bowlers%20will%20bowl%20faster%20due%20to%20the%20benefit%20associated%20with%20increased%20limb%20length.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20as%20limbs%20get%20longer%2C%20they%20get%20more%20difficult%20to%20rotate.%20As%20muscular%20strength%20does%20not%20scale%20equally%20with%20limb%20length%20this%20becomes%20a%20disadvantage.%20Thus%2C%20an%20optimal%20height%20for%20fast%20bowlers%20probably%20exists%2C%20though%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20what%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOrganismic%20factors%20linked%20with%20increased%20ball%20speed%20such%20as%20body%20shape%2C%20size%20and%20hypermobility%20are%20largely%20genetic.%20Since%20human%20evolution%20is%20extremely%20slow%2C%20advances%20in%20ball%20release%20speed%20are%20likely%20to%20follow%20at%20a%20similar%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20100mph%20barrier%2C%20therefore%2C%20should%20be%20viewed%20more%20as%20a%20mountain%20that%20requires%20a%20once-every-generation%20bowler%20to%20scale%20rather%20than%20a%20dam%20in%20a%20river.%20The%20potential%20of%20this%20peak%20to%20grow%20is%20limited%20by%20the%20constraints%20of%20the%20task%20and%20by%20our%20innate%20physiology.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcon