%20and%20even%20gesticulated%20at%20television%20cameras.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20finalising%20its%20report%2C%20which%20will%20be%20submitted%20to%20the%20Speaker%2C%20who%2C%20if%20satisfied%20with%20it%2C%20may%20place%20it%20before%20Lok%20Sabha%20during%20the%20Winter%20Session%20for%20necessary%20action.%20Moitra's%20behaviour%20after%20she%20left%20the%20meeting%2C%20her%20utterances%2C%20and%20the%20statement%20of%20the%20chairman%20and%20members%20of%20the%20panel%20indicate%20that%20apart%20from%20breach%20of%20ethics%2C%20for%20which%20she%20is%20arraigned%2C%20the%20charge%20of%20committing%20an%20act%20of%20contempt%20may%20also%20arise%2C%20throwing%20up%20issues%20related%20to%20the%20privilege%20of%20parliament.%20Larger%20questions%20on%20crony%20capitalism%20may%20also%20emerge.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoitra's%20demeanour%20seemed%20to%20reflect%20Shakespeare's%20words%20in%20Macbeth%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20all%20sound%20and%20fury%2C%20signifying%20nothing%26quot%3B.%20While%20she%20was%20walking%20out%2C%20she%20was%20accompanied%20by%20five%20members%20of%20the%20panel%20belonging%20to%20parties%20constituting%20the%20opposition%20'INDIA'%20alliance%2C%20who%2C%20breaking%20with%20the%20norms%20of%20parliamentary%20committees%2C%20disclosed%20that%20Moitra%20had%20reason%20to%20feel%20chagrined%20by%20the%20'line%20of%20questioning'%20adopted%20by%20Sonkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20his%20part%2C%20Sonkar%2C%20leaving%20after%20the%20disrupted%20proceedings%2C%20told%20reporters%20in%20response%20to%20their%20questions%20that%20Mahua%20Moitra%20had%20displayed%20anger%20and%20used%20unparliamentary%20language%20against%20him%20and%20other%20members.%20The%20BJP's%20Aparijita%20Sarangi%2C%20who%20was%20by%20his%20side%2C%20confirmed%20this%20and%20called%20out%20two%20non-BJP%20MPs%2C%20who%20were%20among%20the%20five%20who%20walked%20out%20with%20Moitra%2C%20for%20filibustering.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fvduqltu8_mahua-moitra-ani-650_650x400_02_November_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EHours%20after%20her%20walkout%2C%20Moitra%2C%20while%20accusing%20Sonkar%20of%20misogyny%2C%20and%20saying%20BJP%20members%20were%20hostile%2C%20expressed%20gratitude%20towards%20the%20two%20women%20BJP%20members%20on%20the%20panel%2C%20Aparijita%20Sarangi%20and%20Sunita%20Duggal%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BThey%20did%20not%20say%20a%20word%26quot%3B.%20TV%20cameras%20have%20recorded%20Aparajita%20Sarangi's%20endorsement%20of%20Sonkar's%20anguish.%20Perhaps%20Moitra's%20hyper%20behaviour%20had%20stunned%20her%20into%20silence%20in%20the%20meeting%20hall.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EParliamentary%20committee%20meetings%20are%20held%20in-camera.%20MPs%20are%20not%20expected%20to%20divide%20on%20party%20lines.%20Unlike%20in%20the%20US%2C%20where%20open%20hearings%20are%20conducted%2C%20the%20media%20only%20learns%20about%20the%20outcome%20of%20these%20meetings%20when%20a%20report%20is%20placed%20on%20the%20table%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Mahua%20Moitra%20case%2C%20all%20rules%20seem%20to%20have%20been%20abandoned.%20First%2C%20Moitra%2C%20who%20was%20deposed%2C%20went%20public.%20Five%20members%20of%20the%20panel%20who%20walked%20out%20with%20her%2C%20while%20endorsing%20her%2C%20breached%20the%20rules.%20Chairman%20Sonkar%20perhaps%20had%20little%20choice%20when%20the%20media%20asked%20questions%2C%20as%20what%20transpired%20inside%20the%20meeting%20room%20had%20been%20laid%20bare%20by%20the%20time%20he%20came%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENishikant%20Dubey%2C%20the%20MP%20on%20whose%20complaint%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20acted%2C%20posted%20on%20'X'%3A%20%26quot%3BChairman%20of%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%2C%20who%20belongs%20to%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%2C%20found%20Mahua's%20language%20abusive.%26quot%3B%20Dubey%20pointed%20out%20that%20Moitra%20had%20referred%20to%20him%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bscoundrel%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20had%20even%20called%20him%20a%20%26quot%3BBihari%20goonda%26quot%3B.%20On%20October%2027%2C%20a%20day%20after%20the%20panel%20summoned%20her%2C%20Moitra%2C%20clarifying%20her%20position%20to%20a%20TV%20anchor%2C%20referred%20to%20a%20%26quot%3BJharkhandi%20Pit%20Bull%26quot%3B.%20Dubey%20represents%20Godda%20in%20Jharkhand.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoitra's%20October%2027%20TV%20interactions%2C%20recorded%20at%20her%20New%20Delhi%20residence%2C%20made%20the%20panel%20insist%20on%20November%202%20as%20the%20date%20of%20hearing.%20Earlier%2C%20when%20the%20summons%20was%20issued%2C%20Moitra%20had%20pleaded%20that%20she%20was%20busy%20with%20post-Dussehra%20events%20in%20her%20constituency%20till%20November%205%2C%20and%20the%20panel%20seemed%20inclined%20to%20wait.%20Her%20presence%20in%20New%20Delhi%20was%20at%20variance%20with%20her%20plea%20for%20postponement%20and%20the%20panel%20chairman%20was%20quick%20to%20set%20up%20the%20hearing%20as%20the%20panel%20is%20expected%20to%20report%20back%20to%20the%20Speaker%20expeditiously.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20November%202%2C%20apparently%2C%20the%20two%20pre-lunch%20hours%20were%20utilised%20by%20Moitra%20to%20state%20her%20case.%20In%20her%20defamation%20case%20against%20complainant%20Jai%20Anant%20Dehadrai%20(whom%20she%20refers%20to%20as%20a%20'jilted-ex')%20and%20Dubey%2C%20she%20has%20referred%20to%20her%20personal%20life%2C%20and%20apparently%2C%20her%20testimony%20on%20November%202%20focused%20on%20the%20same%20argument.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20post-lunch%20session%2C%20based%20on%20her%20testimony%2C%20questions%20related%20to%20her%20personal%20life%20figured.%20This%20infuriated%20her.%20Chairman%20Sonkar%20had%20a%20report%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20ministry%2C%20which%20listed%2047%20occasions%20when%20Moitra's%20Lok%20Sabha%20ID%20and%20password%20had%20been%20accessed%20from%20overseas%2C%20in%20Dubai.%20As%20the%20use%20of%20the%20portal%20for%20parliamentary%20questions%20entails%20an%20OTP%20on%20the%20MP's%20phone%20for%20verification%2C%20a%20number%20of%20short-duration%20phone%20calls%20made%20late%20at%20night%2C%20coinciding%20with%20the%20OTPs%20(perhaps%20the%20calls%20shared%20the%20OTP%20)%20were%20also%20on%20Sonkar's%20agenda.%20Moitra%20was%20enraged%20and%20alleged%20that%20a%20lady's%20late-night%20phone%20calls%20were%20being%20pried%20on.%20And%20instead%20of%20clarifying%20her%20position%2C%20she%20stomped%20out.%20The%20fact%20that%20she%20did%20share%20her%20parliamentary%20log-in%20details%20with%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%2C%20a%20businessman%2C%20was%20not%20denied.%20In%20her%20media%20interviews%2C%20she%20has%20admitted%20to%20having%20done%20so.%20Her%20plea%20is%20that%20she%20represents%20a%20'remote'%20constituency%20and%20was%20using%20the%20secretarial%20services%20of%20Hiranandani's%20office%20to%20dictate%20questions%2C%20which%20were%20thereafter%20filed%20with%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20secretariat%20from%20Dubai.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoitra%20represents%20Krishnagar%2C%20which%20is%20around%20100%20kilometres%20from%20Kolkata%2C%20a%20four-hour%20drive%20along%20National%20Highway%2012.%20Krishnagar%20is%20part%20of%20Kolkata's%20suburban%20rail%20system.%20The%20apparently%20well-educated%20Mahua%20Moitra%2C%20who%20is%20computer%20savvy%2C%20could%20not%20find%20a%20reliable%20steno-typist%20within%20Indian%20shores%20and%20thus%20relied%20upon%20Hirnandani's%20secretary%20in%20Dubai.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20sharing%20her%20log-in%20details%2C%20this%20US-educated%20MP%20overlooked%20Rule%207.2%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BE-mail%20policy%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%26quot%3B%2C%20published%20in%202014%2C%20which%20prohibits%20the%20user%20of%20a%20portal%20run%20by%20the%20National%20Informatics%20Centre%20(NIC)%20from%20%26quot%3B%20sharing%20password%20details%26quot%3B.%20It%20states%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Buser%20is%20responsible%20for%20any%20data%2Fe-mail%20that%20is%20transmitted%26quot%3B.%20A%20copy%20of%20the%20policy%20document%20is%20shared%20with%20all%20users%2C%20including%20MPs%20when%20they%20are%20granted%20access%20by%20NIC.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoitra%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20panel%20of%20parliament.%20Hiranandani%20is%20in%20the%20IT%20sector.%20The%20hypothecation%20of%20her%20ID%20therefore%20also%20opens%20up%20the%20possibility%20of%20Hiranandani%20gaining%20access%20to%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20panel%2C%20in%20which%20the%20government%20shares%20classified%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDehadrai's%20testimony%20reveals%20that%20apart%20from%20the%20Hiranandani%20factor%2C%20in%20which%20Moitra%20allowed%20a%20businessman%20to%20post%2051%20questions%20on%20his%20rivals%2C%20the%20Hindenburg%20report%2C%20which%20shook%20the%20foundations%20of%20India's%20stock%20market%20and%20caused%20a%20huge%20loss%20to%20many%20common%20shareholders%2C%20contained%20five%20direct%20references%20to%20complaints%20filed%20by%20Moitra%20on%20the%20Adani%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20the%20Hindenburg%20report%2C%20while%20India's%20small%20investors%20suffered%20losses%2C%20short-sellers%20made%20crores%20of%20rupees%20by%20going%20short%20just%20before%20the%20report%20surfaced.%20Identifying%20these%20short-sellers%20and%20their%20accomplices%20is%20imperative%20to%20the%20future%20health%20of%20India's%20economy.%20Could%20there%20have%20been%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20behind%20those%20who%20cooperated%20with%20Hindenburg%20and%20the%20profiteering%20by%20short-sellers%3F%20This%20is%20the%20interesting%20collateral%20of%20l'affaire%20Mahua%20Moitra.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Ethics%20Committee%20has%20a%20yeoman%20task%20on%20hand.%20The%20findings%20in%20the%20Mahua%20Moitra%20case%20will%20have%20long-term%20repercussions%20on%20the%20functioning%20of%20India's%20parliament%20and%20polity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Shubhabrata%20Bhattacharya%20is%20a%20retired%20Editor%20and%20a%20public%20affairs%20commentator.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699192080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fptunpgqo_mahua-moitra-pti_625x300_28_October_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fmahua-moitras-conduct-compounds-ethics-case-will-it-attract-contempt-4547925%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mahua%20Moitra%20may%20have%20lost%20her%20opportunity%20to%20defend%20her%20conduct%20before%20Lok%20Sabha's%20Ethics%20Committee%20with%20her%20behaviour%20during%20the%20proceedings%20and%20her%20subsequent%20stomping%20out%20of%20the%20room%20heaping%20allegations%20against%20the%20panel's%20chairman%20to%20the%20media.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fmahua-moitras-conduct-compounds-ethics-case-will-it-attract-contempt-4547925%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ukraine%20war%20not%20at%20'stalemate'%2C%20Zelenskyy%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699191840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-volodymyr-zelenskyy_6324595.jpg%3F20231017144053%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fukraine-war-not-a-stalemate-volodymyr-zelenskyy-says-13001159%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20has%20rejected%20claims%20the%20war%20with%20Russia%20is%20at%20a%20%26quot%3Bstalemate%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A514%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fukraine-war-not-a-stalemate-volodymyr-zelenskyy-says-13001159%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%