%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Finance%20Ministry%20Authorises%20Sale%20of%2029th%20Batch%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Two%20Days%20After%20SC%20Hearings%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F05141137%2FState-Bank-of-India.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Authorised%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20branches%20across%20the%20country%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1974675%5C%22%3Emay%20issue%20electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20Monday%20(November%206)%20and%20November%2020%2C%20the%20Union%20finance%20ministry%20announced%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20be%20the%2029th%20batch%20of%20electoral%20bond%20sales%20since%20the%20BJP-led%20Union%20government%20introduced%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftag%2Felectoral-bonds%5C%22%3Escheme%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20finance%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20announcement%20came%20two%20days%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F1058545%2Fsupreme-court-reserves-judgement-in-electoral-bonds-case%5C%22%3Ereserved%20its%20verdict%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20batch%20of%20pleas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-sc-questions-anonymity-of-electoral-bonds-and-voters-right-to-information%5C%22%3Echallenging%20the%20validity%20of%20electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20weeks%20ahead%20of%20assembly%20elections%20in%20five%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EElectoral%20bonds%20are%20interest-free%20financial%20instruments%20that%20individuals%20or%20groups%20may%20use%20to%20make%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20issued%20by%20authorised%20SBI%20branches%20in%20discrete%20amounts%20ranging%20between%20Rs%201%2C000%20and%20Rs%201%20crore%20after%20payment%20via%20cheque%20or%20digital%20means.%20Payment%20via%20cash%20is%20not%20allowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EParties%20need%20to%20be%20registered%20and%20have%20received%20at%20least%201%25%20of%20the%20vote%20in%20the%20last%20parliamentary%20or%20assembly%20election%20in%20order%20to%20receive%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20proposed%20the%20scheme%20in%202017%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fjaitley-political-funding-reforms-budget-anonymous-donations%5C%22%3Esaying%20it%20would%20bring%20much-needed%20transparency%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20how%20parties%20are%20funded%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20critics%20have%20argued%20that%20the%20anonymous%20nature%20of%20donations%20through%20the%20scheme%20violates%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20information%20about%20funding%20of%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-62991256%5C%22%3Eraised%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20may%20access%20SBI%20data%20about%20the%20identity%20of%20electoral%20bond%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felectoral-bonds-fatf-report-bjp-constitution%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20Contrary%20to%20PMLA%2C%20Favours%20Ruling%20Party%E2%80%99%3A%20Coalition%20Report%20Tells%20FATF%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAttorney%20general%20R.%20Venkataramani%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcitizens-have-no-fundamental-right-to-know-of-source-of-political-funding-ag-to-sc%5C%22%3Esubmitted%20last%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20citizens%20have%20no%20fundamental%20right%20to%20know%20the%20sources%20of%20electoral%20bond%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20can%20be%20no%20general%20right%20to%20know%20anything%20and%20everything%20without%20being%20subjected%20to%20reasonable%20restrictions%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fcitizens-dont-have-right-to-information-regarding-funding-of-a-political-party-centre-tells-supreme-court-in-electoral-bonds-case-241137%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20later%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20began%20hearing%20four%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20validity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioners%20urged%20the%20court%20to%20declare%20political%20parties%20as%20public%20offices%20to%20bring%20them%20under%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%20and%20to%20compel%20them%20to%20disclose%20their%20income%20and%20expenditure.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20who%20was%20on%20the%20constitution%20bench%20hearing%20the%20matter%2C%20said%20that%20the%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20provision%20for%20anonymous%20donations%20may%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsc-flags-possibility-of-electoral-bonds-being-used-by-the-rich-to-covertly-trade-favours-with-parties-in-power%2Farticle67480930.ece%5C%22%3Eaimed%20at%20preventing%20repercussions%20from%20parties%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20which%20a%20person%20or%20entity%20has%20not%20donated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSuppose%20you%20are%20contributing%20to%20a%20party%20not%20in%20power%E2%80%A6%20suppose%20the%20donor%20is%20carrying%20on%20business%20in%20the%20state%20and%20his%20name%20is%20made%20available%20to%20all%E2%80%A6%20There%20is%20logic%20there%3B%20whether%20it%20is%20valid%20or%20not%2C%20we%20have%20to%20decide%2C%E2%80%9D%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKapil%20Sibal%2C%20counsel%20for%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%2C%20also%20told%20the%20bench%20that%20there%20is%20no%20regulation%20in%20the%20scheme%20that%20specifically%20ties%20funding%20received%20by%20bonds%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Felectoral-bonds-case-supreme-court-begins-hearing-case-that-goes-to-the-root-of-democracy%2F%5C%22%3Euses%20for%20electoral%20purposes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Felectoral-bonds-transparency-in-political-funding%5C%22%3EMuch%20Ado%20About%20Nothing%3A%20Electoral%20Bonds%20and%20an%20Unapologetic%20Lack%20of%20Transparency%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20make%20a%20donation%20of%20%E2%82%B910%20crore%20to%20a%20political%20party%20through%20electoral%20bonds%E2%80%A6%20The%20party%20can%20give%20it%20to%20a%20mainstream%20media%20channel%20and%20propagate%20my%20ideology%20or%20give%20a%20present%20to%20someone.%20I%20have%20no%20control%20over%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Leaflet%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20hearing%20the%20petitions%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20and%20asked%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F1058545%2Fsupreme-court-reserves-judgement-in-electoral-bonds-case%5C%22%3Ecollect%20data%20on%20donations%20received%20by%20parties%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20until%20September%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20conducted%20an%20analysis%20of%20electoral%20bond%20funding%20using%20data%20provided%20by%20the%20Association%20of%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%2C%20which%20was%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%20from%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20found%20that%20%3Cspan%3Enot%20only%20did%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fafter-electoral-bonds-income-from-unknown-sources-to-political-parties-rose-to-72-of-total-income%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20share%20of%20national%20parties%E2%80%99%20income%20through%20unknown%20sources%20increase%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20since%20electoral%20bonds%20wer