%20Patel%20explained%20that%20the%20painting%20was%20inspired%20by%20his%20memory%20of%20village%20wells%20in%20his%20native%20Gujarat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20seaside%20village%20and%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20wells%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20the%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20are%20not%20huge%20step%20wells%2C%20but%20are%20smaller%2C%20more%20modest.%20In%20the%20monsoon%2C%20they%20fill%20right%20up%20to%20the%20brim.%20As%20a%20child%2C%20I%20spent%20quite%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20looking%20into%20them%20and%20that%20habit%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20quite%20gone.%20Even%20now%2C%20whenever%20I%20pass%20a%20well%2C%20I%20feel%20compelled%20to%20look%20into%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fartiana.com%2FGieve-Patel%2Fgr5uo%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fartiana.com%2FGieve-Patel%2Fgr5uo%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1699243599902000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0VmqBsfD04vWLsCafT2J76%5C%22%3Ecatalogue%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%20accompanying%20the%20painting%2C%20Patel%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%9CLooking%20into%20a%20well%20is%20a%20delight%20to%20the%20senses%20at%20any%20time%20of%20day%20or%20night.%20It%20is%20also%20a%20rehearsal%20for%20looking%20into%20the%20depths%20of%20oneself.%E2%80%9D%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20all%20of%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20work%20%E2%80%93%20as%20a%20poet%2C%20painter%2C%20playwright%2C%20or%20physician%20%E2%80%93%20was%20an%20act%20of%20looking%20into%20depths%2C%20real%20or%20metaphysical%2C%20with%20curiosity%20and%20courage.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EGieve%20Patel%20(1940-2023)%2C%20Early%20Morning%20Local%2C%201981.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FojWoEjlXoM%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FojWoEjlXoM%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Prathyush%20Parasuraman%20(%40geekoutyush)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fgeekoutyush%2Fstatus%2F1720498144314847240%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ENovember%203%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20key%20figures%20of%20post-Independence%20Indian%20poetry%20in%20English%2C%20Patel%20succumbed%20to%20cancer%20on%20the%20afternoon%20of%20Friday%2C%C2%A0%20November%203%2C%20at%20Cipla%20Palliative%20Care%20and%20Training%20Centre%20in%20Pune%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fpune%2Fgieve-patel-doctor-and-poet-passes-away-at-83%2Farticleshow%2F104957076.cms%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fpune%2Fgieve-patel-doctor-and-poet-passes-away-at-83%2Farticleshow%2F104957076.cms%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1699243599902000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1wYW9zDcOmCHo83dzNVZ6I%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%C2%A0%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20was%2083%20and%20is%20survived%20by%20a%20daughter.%20As%20news%20of%20his%20death%20spread%20among%20poetry%20lovers%2C%20several%20writers%20who%20knew%20him%2C%20took%20to%20social%20media%20to%20express%20their%20grief.%20Ashwani%20Kumar%2C%20poet%20and%20professor%20at%20Tata%20Institute%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20Mumbai%2C%20posted%20a%20picture%20with%20Patel%20on%20Instagram%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCzN9RIfM1PBL3Ky4z0H_qBeVeTj66dtHtjMSM80%2F%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCzN9RIfM1PBL3Ky4z0H_qBeVeTj66dtHtjMSM80%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1699243599902000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3tlVZb3tv44lU2_3zGOMrj%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CCan%E2%80%99t%20imagine%20life%20of%20poetry%20in%20Mumbai%20without%20Gieve%E2%80%A6%20Ah!%20All%20seven%20islands%20grieving%20together!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPoet%20and%20translator%20Sampurna%20Chattarji%20also%20posted%20a%20picture%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCzMPAClyBgZ%2F%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCzMPAClyBgZ%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1699243599902000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1YcFAKOvq8KNdPWdaLs_hj%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CThat%20dry%20chuckle%2C%20the%20impish%20grin%2C%20despite%20the%20cough.%20Too%20much%20to%20process.%20He%20went%20in%20grace.%20The%20way%20he%20lived.%E2%80%9D%20Poet%20and%20translator%20Ranjit%20Hoskote%2C%20who%20is%20also%20an%20art%20critic%2C%20posted%20a%20picture%20with%20Patel%2C%20Sudhir%20Pathwardhan%20(with%20whom%20Patel%20had%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2006%2F02%2F24%2Farts%2Fart-in-review-gieve-patel-and-sudhir-patwardhan.html%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2006%2F02%2F24%2Farts%2Fart-in-review-gieve-patel-and-sudhir-patwardhan.html%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1699243599902000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0j4oq3QegFXMLgcOmMV3ag%5C%22%3Ejoint%20exhibition%20in%20New%20York%20in%202006%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20and%20art%20critic%20Nancy%20Adjania.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20always%20remember%20Gieve%20like%20this%3A%20bright%2C%20wickedly%20witty%2C%20sharp%20in%20his%20insight%20into%20human%20nature%2C%20sympathetic%20but%20never%20soppy%2C%20his%20stoic%20wisdom%20held%20in%20counterpoint%20by%20his%20baleful%20refusal%20to%20suffer%20fools%20and%20his%20uproarious%2C%20infectious%20laughter%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCzOX-m0II8o%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_web_copy_link%26igshid%3DMzRlODBiNWFlZA%3D%3D%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCzOX-m0II8o%2F%3Futm_source%253Dig_web_copy_link%2526igshid%253DMzRlODBiNWFlZA%253D%253D%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1699243599902000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3VBxTDcjUlK3sk_X94FMh8%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ERIP%20Gieve%20Patel%2C%20a%20great%20poet%20who%20was%20deeply%20attentive%20to%20non-human%20worlds.%20His%20poem%20%E2%80%9COn%20Killing%20a%20Tree%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20classic.%3Cbr%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FjFv7zT8BA5%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FjFv7zT8BA5%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fo7VzTkczbB%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fo7VzTkczbB%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Amitav%20Ghosh%20(%40GhoshAmitav)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FGhoshAmitav%2Fstatus%2F1720712339920478621%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ENovember%204%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%20Patel%20was%20born%20in%201940%20in%20Mumbai%20(then%20known%20as%20Bombay).%20His%20father%20was%20a%20dentist%20and%20his%20mother%20the%20daughter%20of%20a%20doctor.%20The%20family%20originated%20in%20the%20village%20of%20Nargol%20in%20Gujarat.%20The%20practice%20of%20medicine%20in%20the%20family%20inspired%20his%20decision%20to%20become%20a%20doctor.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20grandfather%2C%20the%20village%20doctor%2C%20was%20a%20happy%20influence%2C%E2%80%9D%20Patel%20told%20literary%20scholar%20Anjali%20Nerlekar%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F17449855.2017.1294647%3Fcasa_token%3DyC4D-fr2vXMAAAAA%253AXjqp6gxNBcUEgCDZ9ZOHjsOFjROO3h9H6j0fiAkLHEJAZM51wEBFxOE3YIrqa7KvRlIOadgdxKz-pT-m%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F17449855.2017.1294647%3Fcasa_token%253DyC4D-fr2vXMAAAAA%25253AXjqp6gxNBcUEgCDZ9ZOHjsOFjROO3h9H6j0fiAkLHEJAZM51wEBFxOE3YIrqa7KvRlIOadgdxKz-pT-m%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1699243599902000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3YQcFQUKZz16H1zTSOtnsL%5C%22%3Ea%202017%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20would%20take%20me%20on%20night%20visits%20to%20patients%E2%80%99%20home%20in%20a%20tonga.%20It%20was%20an%20amazing%20experience%20as%20a%20child.%20Maybe%20the%20impulse%20to%20become%20a%20doctor%20came%20from%20here.%E2%80%9D%20The%20practice%20of%20medicine%20possibly%20inspired%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20depictions%20of%20the%20human%20body%20in%20both%20his%20poetry%20and%20his%20paintings.%20%E2%80%9C(H)is%20work%20views%20the%20human%20body%20as%20%E2%80%98a%20target%20of%20violence%3A%20the%20violence%20is%20seen%20to%20emanate%20from%20the%20state%20as%20well%20as%20the%20psyche%20of%20each%20individual%2C%E2%80%9D%20claims%20his%20biographical%20note%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Penguin%20Book%20of%20Indian%20Poets%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2022)%2C%20edited%20by%20Jeet%20Thayil.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20his%20best%20known%20poems%2C%20%E2%80%98On%20Killing%20a%20Tree%E2%80%99%2C%20perhaps%20best%20describes%20this%20violence%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20takes%20much%20time%20to%20kill%20a%20tree%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENot%20a%20simple%20jab%20of%20the%20knife%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWill%20do%20it.%20It%20has%20grown%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESlowly%20consuming%20the%20earth%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERising%20out%20of%20it%2C%20feeding%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUpon%20its%20crust%2C%20absorbing%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYears%20of%20sunlight%2C%20air%2C%20water%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20out%20of%20its%20leprous%20hide%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESprouting%20leaves.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20hack%20and%20chop%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20alone%20won%E2%80%99t%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENot%20so%20much%20pain%20will%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bleeding%20bark%20will%20heal%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20from%20close%20to%20the%20ground%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWill%20rise%20curled%20green%20twigs%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMiniature%20boughs%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhich%20if%20unchecked%20will%20expand%20again%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20former%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENo%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20root%20is%20to%20be%20pulled%20out%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%20anchoring%20earth%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20to%20be%20roped%2C%20tied%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20pulled%20out%20%E2%80%93%20snapped%20out%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOr%20pulled%20out%20entirely%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOut%20from%20the%20earth-cave%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20tree%20exposed%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20source%2C%20white%20and%20wet%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20sensitive%2C%20hidden%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20years%20inside%20the%20earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20our%20country%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20escape%20being%20hit%20all%20the%20time%20by%20the%20physical%20aspect%20of%20things%2C%E2%80%9D%20Patel%20told%20Nerlekar.%20%E2%80%9CBecause%20of%20the%20weather%20people%20don%E2%80%99t%20cover%20themselves%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20heavy%20clothing%2C%20so%20the%20body%2C%20its%20beauty%20and%20its%20ugliness%2C%20is%20always%20available%20for%20viewing.%20Second%2C%20the%20body%20is%20subjected%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20trauma%20%E2%80%93%20illness%2C%20injury%20%E2%80%93%20so%20it%20seems%20to%20me%20it%20would%20be%20unnatural%20not%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20it.%E2%80%9D%20Patel%20and%20his%20contemporaries%20approached%20the%20human%20body%20with%20%E2%80%9Ca%20certain%20degree%20of%20objectivity%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20he%20described%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Caromatic%20approach.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20aromantic%20%E2%80%93%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20say%20anti-romantic%20%E2%80%93%20an%20aromantic%20approach%20that%20our%20generation%20arrived%20at.%20It%20meant%20that%20we%20were%20going%20to%20look%20at%20what%20was%20around%20us%20with%20a%20certain%20degree%20of%20objectivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20Patel%20started%20writing%20poetry%20when%20he%20was%2016%20years%20old%2C%20his%20first%20book%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EPoems%3C%2Fem%3E%20would%20be%20published%20in%201966%20%E2%80%93%20also%20the%20year%20of%20his%20first%20exhibition%20at%20the%20Jehangir%20Art%20Gallery%20in%20Mumbai%20%E2%80%93%20under%20the%20mentorship%20of%20Nissim%20Ezekiel.%20But%20when%20he%20first%20met%20Ezekiel%20in%201959%2C%20the%20latter%20was%20not%20very%20impressed%20with%20young%20poet%E2%80%99s%20work.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20he%20said%20he%20would%20like%20to%20see%20the%20next%20batch%20of%20poems%20when%20ready%2C%E2%80%9D%20Patel%20told%20Nerlekar.%20%E2%80%9CSo%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20later%20I%20showed%20him%20the%20new%20poems.%20He%20responded%20well%20to%20these.%20Later%2C%20some%20of%20these%20poems%20were%20included%20in%20my%20first%20collection.%E2%80%9D%20He%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CNissim%20published%20that%20first%20book%E2%80%A6%20And%20Nissim%20was%20also%20the%20art%20critic%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0so%20he%20reviewed%20my%20art%20show%20too.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBombay%20was%20an%20exciting%20place%20for%20a%20young%20writer%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20whether%20they%20wrote%20in%20English%20or%20other%20languages%20like%20Marathi%20or%20Gujarati.%20The%20presence%20of%20a%20large%20number%20of%20artists%2C%20poets%2C%20and%20performers%20in%20the%20city%2C%20which%20has%20been%20described%20by%20publisher%20David%20Davidar%20in%20his%20novel%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Solitude%20of%20Emperors%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2007)%3A%20%E2%80%9CA%20city%20of%20poets%20and%20caf%C3%A9s%2C%20and%20all-night%20sessions%20of%20drinking%20and%20versifying%2C%20a%20place%20to%20rival%20Joyce%E2%80%99s%20Dublin%20or%20Cavafy%E2%80%99s%20Alexandria%20or%20Pessoa%E2%80%99s%20Lisbon%3A%20Dom%20(Moraes)%20hammering%20away%20with%20one%20finger%20at%20his%20typewriter%20in%20Sargent%20House%2C%20spectacles%20slipping%20down%20his%20nose%2C%20as%20the%20poems%20ran%20wild%20in%20his%20head%2C%20Adil%20(Jussawala)%20holding%20court%20in%20his%20eyrie%20on%20Cuffe%20Parade%2C%20Nissim%20(Ezekiel)%20spinning%20his%20demotic%20verse%20in%20coffee%20houses%20and%20poets%E2%80%99%20gathering%2C%20(Arun)%20Kolatkar%20with%20his%20strange%20fierce%20epic%20about%20Gods%20of%20stone.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20poetry%20of%20this%20period%20was%20also%20rooted%2C%20albeit%20sometimes%20obliquely%2C%20in%20the%20sociopolitical%20climate%20of%20the%20time%2C%20and%20must%20be%20read%20against%20defining%20political%20events%20and%20circumstances%20such%20as%20the%20Emergency%20(1975%E2%80%9377)%20and%20the%20context%20of%20the%20cultural%20Cold%20War%E2%80%A6%20but%20also%20the%20Dalit%20movement%2C%20whose%20literature%20sparked%20the%20renewal%20of%20Marathi%20language%20and%20literary%20culture%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F17449855.2017.1298505%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F17449855.2017.1298505%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1699243599903000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0CzyMdnqnbK1fEODXdtcCy%5C%22%3Ewrite%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0literary%20scholars%20Nerlekar%20and%20Laetitia%20Zecchini%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20have%20done%20pioneering%20work%20in%20exploring%20mid-20th-century%20Bombay%20as%20a%20space%20for%20Indian%20modernity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20products%20of%20this%20culture%20was%20Clearing%20House%2C%20a%20publishing%20cooperative%20set%20up%20by%20Patel%2C%20and%20his%20contemporaries%20Arun%20Kolatkar%2C%20Adil%20Jussawalla%2C%20and%20Arvind%20Krishna%20Mehrotra.%20In%202010%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcaravanmagazine.in%2Fessay%2Fyour-missing-person-clearing-house-and-bombay-poets%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fcaravanmagazine.in%2Fessay%2Fyour-missing-person-clearing-house-and-bombay-poets%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1699243599903000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3T7X1XwZRVhyZeGwBiEyIj%5C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Mehrotra%20told%20novelist%20Anjum%20Hasan%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eraison%20d%E2%80%99etre%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Efor%20setting%20up%20the%20collective%3A%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20early%201970s%20we%20all%20realised%20that%20we%20had%20manuscripts.%20There%20were%20no%20publishers.%20Then%20Oxford%20University%20Press%20under%20R%20Parthasarathy%20started%20the%20New%20Poetry%20in%20India%20series.%20Some%20titles%20did%20appear%20under%20that.%20But%20what%20would%20happen%20to%20the%20others%3F%20We%20decided%20not%20to%20wait%20and%20formed%20a%20co-operative.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EGieve%20Patel%20was%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20Bombay%20poets.%20RIP.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FvJK1lo2wXB%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FvJK1lo2wXB%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FmtkYbLaZyy%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FmtkYbLaZyy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Bilal%20Moin%20(%40TheBilalMoin)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTheBilalMoin%2Fstatus%2F1720468615470674198%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ENovember%203%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20very%20first%20year%20of%20its%20existence%2C%20Clearing%20House%20published%20four%20books%20%E2%80%93%20Arun%20Kolatkar%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EJejuri%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Arvind%20Krishna%20Mehrotra%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENine%20Enclosures%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Adil%20Jussawalla%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMissing%20Person%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20Gieve%20Patel%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHow%20Do%20You%20Withstand%2C%20Body%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20also%20published%20Dilip%20Chitre%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3ETravelling%20in%20a%20Cage%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%20Jayanta%20Mahapatra%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20False%20Start%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0in%201980%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Arvind%20Krishna%20Mehrotra%E2%80%99s%20Distance%20in%20Statute%20Miles%20(1982)%20and%20H.%20O.%20Nazareth%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3ELobo%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(1984)%20before%20folding%20up%20because%20of%20lack%20of%20money.%20Despite%20its%20short%20existence%2C%20however%2C%20both%20Clearing%20House%20and%20the%20poets%20associated%20with%20it%20have%20become%20legends%20of%20sorts%20in%20Indian%20literature.%20Patel%20published%20a%20third%20book%20of%20poems%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMirrored%2C%20Mirroring%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20with%20Oxford%20University%20Press%20in%201991.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBesides%20poetry%2C%20Patel%20also%20wrote%20three%20plays%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EPrinces%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(1970)%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESavaksa%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(1982)%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMister%20Behram%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(1988).%20All%20of%20them%20are%20located%20in%20Parsi%20culture%2C%20with%20which%20he%20was%20most%20familiar%2C%20though%20he%20was%20unhappy%20with%20the%20tag%20of%20%E2%80%9CParsi%20playwright%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20you%20should%20label%20it%20as%20a%20Parsi%20play%2C%20though%20it%20is%20written%20by%20a%20Parsi%20and%20filled%20with%20Parsi%20characters%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fliteraturecurry.com%2Fuploads%2Fpdfnotes%2F1040648d-96e6-46e2-b02e-d38cf892c670_CYRUS%2520MISTRY.pdf%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fliteraturecurry.com%2Fuploads%2Fpdfnotes%2F1040648d-96e6-46e2-b02e-d38cf892c670_CYRUS%252520MISTRY.pdf%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1699243599903000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0hg1nZlmmDcSzQq6mg6TcE%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0an%20interviewer.%20Literary%20scholar%20Bruce%20King%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmuse.jhu.edu%2Fpub%2F124%2Farticle%2F477861%2Fsummary%3Fcasa_token%3D0pKUGcJSEC4AAAAA%3ADfGIXhzxOaYJ7C7ETwJNwpCKHUsQpwCIbxfEmIYt9Lc2oxLeW3aT0NBEVw96GSV48fQKx3nzNqc%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fmuse.jhu.edu%2Fpub%2F124%2Farticle%2F477861%2Fs