ocially%20marginal%20to%20the%20point%20of%20being%20invisible.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ETwo%20Men%20with%20Handcart%20de%20Gieve%20Patel%2C%201979.%20R%20IP%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FFxqF9QqCrN%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FFxqF9QqCrN%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Richa%20Roy%20(%40The_RichaRoy)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FThe_RichaRoy%2Fstatus%2F1720463869838274804%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ENovember%203%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20recollects%20in%20his%20interview%20with%20Nerlekar%2C%20Patel%20learnt%20to%20paint%20himself%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20started%20by%20copying%20reproductions%20from%20books%2C%20and%20colouring%20them.%20Then%20I%20began%20going%20to%20the%20Jehangir%20Art%20Gallery%20to%20meet%20some%20of%20the%20artists%20there.%E2%80%9D%20Akbar%20Padamsee%20became%20a%20mentor%20to%20him.%20In%20another%20essay%2C%20Patel%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F09528822.2017.1396688%3Fcasa_token%3Diugy7Z_4DoQAAAAA%253ABcvd-MAb_z8EmVl-fuKVIZ8rVabqA_7c8wwRmZ-HDho-at6AmpxHPbE3x-QM7CVZd2vy3Cc9I1m9uP3v%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F09528822.2017.1396688%3Fcasa_token%253Diugy7Z_4DoQAAAAA%25253ABcvd-MAb_z8EmVl-fuKVIZ8rVabqA_7c8wwRmZ-HDho-at6AmpxHPbE3x-QM7CVZd2vy3Cc9I1m9uP3v%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1699243599903000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1pXkUo3HWUIAQSKDj0WVS6%5C%22%3Ewrites%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CPost-Independence%20India%20had%20no%20role%20for%20the%20urban%2C%20contemporary%20artist%2C%20the%20man%20who%20would%20fabricate%20and%20comment%20upon%20the%20present%2C%20and%20who%20would%20not%20necessarily%20continue%20with%20folk%20and%20classical%20forms.%E2%80%9D%20Patel%2C%20Patwardhan%2C%20and%20several%20of%20his%20contemporaries%20Bhupen%20Khakhar%20represented%20in%20their%20paintings%20the%20point%20of%20view%20of%20marginal%20figures%2C%20but%20devoid%20of%20any%20sentimentality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20of%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20famous%20paintings%20is%C2%A0%3Cem%3ECrows%20with%20Debris%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2000)%2C%20which%20shows%20a%20couple%20of%20crows%20snatching%20the%20remains%20of%20a%20rat%E2%80%99s%20body%20from%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20beaks.%20%E2%80%9CPatel%20commented%20in%20an%20interview%20that%20one%20thing%20he%20values%20about%20Bombay%20over%20the%20antiseptic%20cities%20of%20the%20West%20is%20that%20it%20does%20not%20hide%20its%20dead%2C%20so%20that%20death%20can%20remain%20a%20part%20of%20everyday%20life%20experience%2C%E2%80%9D%20writes%20Zitzewitza.%20In%201984%2C%20Patel%20accused%20Patwardhan%20of%20editing%20out%20the%20squalor%20of%20the%20city%20from%20his%20paintings%2C%20so%20that%20people%20could%20lead%20their%20lives%20with%20some%20hope.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Patel%2C%20a%20doctor%20perhaps%20more%20familiar%20with%20the%20frailties%20of%20the%20human%20body%2C%20editing%20away%20any%20suffering%20is%20unthinkable.%20For%20him%2C%20it%20is%20human%20to%20experience%20and%20represent%20in%20his%20art%20and%20his%20poetry.%20Oh%2C%20it%20is%20all%20too%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUttaran%20Das%20Gupta%20is%20a%20New%20Delhi-based%20writer%20and%20journalist.%20He%20teaches%20journalism%20at%20O.%20P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20Sonipat.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699167175000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F05120339%2FUntitled-design-7.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fgieve-patel-poet-painter-obituary%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20poet%2C%20painter%2C%20playwright%2C%20and%20physician%20was%20a%20vital%20member%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Clearing%20House%E2%80%99%20generation%20of%20Bombay%20